---
title: Charred Zucchini over Bruschetta Spaghetti with Balsamic Drizzle & Parmesan
description: Zucchini fact: Because this squash is 94% water, you can slice shallow cuts into its surface, salt it to draw out extra moisture, then dry it off with paper towels to improve its texture. High heat plus a short cooking time helps it char without getting too squishy! You’ll take that perfectly charred zucchini (brushed with garlic oil) and nestle it atop creamy Parmesan spaghetti along with a bruschetta-style fresh tomato and parsley sauce. Drizzle it with a tangy-sweet balsamic glaze and sprinkle on the Parmesan and chopped parsley for a trattoria-worthy pasta dinner.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/655b7424d1348f59373b1b7b-a612f0d6.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/655b7424d1348f59373b1b7b.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/charred-zucchini-over-bruschetta-spaghetti-655b7424d1348f59373b1b7b
course: main course
servings: 2
author: Sara Heilman
time required: 45 minutes
cuisine: Southern Europe
nutrition:
  calories: 840 kcal
  fat: 44 g
  saturated fat: 19 g
  carbohydrates: 92 g
